When the front bumper is damaged or deformed due to an accident or contact with other objects, etc., or the bumper installation area on the body is repaired, it is necessary to perform millimeter wave radar sensor adjustment.

PROCEDURE

1. PRECAUTION

(a) Change the grille shutter control mode to maintenance mode.

Click here

NOTICE:

Make sure to change the grille shutter control mode to maintenance mode to prevent the grill shutter from opening or closing when the power switch is off.

2. REMOVE RADIATOR SUPPORT OPENING COVER

(a) Remove the 5 clips.

(b) Disengage the 2 guides and remove the radiator support opening cover as shown in the illustration.
